title: Equivalent formulations of Fermat's Last Theorem

blocks.name: dffltz
blocks.content: Fermat's Last Theorem (FLT) for non-zero integers is equivalent to the original scope of natural numbers. The backwards direction takes ` ( a ^ n ) + ( b ^ n ) = ( c ^ n ) ` , and adds the negative of any negative term to both sides, thus creating the corresponding equation with only positive integers. There are six combinations of negativity, so the proof is particularly long. (Contributed by Steven Nguyen, 27-Feb-2023.)

blocks.name: fltne
blocks.content: If a counterexample to FLT exists, its addends are not equal. (Contributed by Steven Nguyen, 1-Jun-2023.)
blocks.origin:
thm fltne(class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wne(c0, c1))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, cn))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c1, cn))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c2, cn))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c3, cfv(cuz, nat3)))
  -| wi(w0, wceq(co(co(c0, cexp, c3), caddc, co(c1, cexp, c3)), co(c2, cexp, c3)))
} = {
  a1ii(wi(w0, wne(c0, c1)), wi(w0, wcel(c1, cn)))
  mteqand(c0, c1, co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), co(c2, cdiv, c0), w0)
  mpd(w0, wne(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), co(c2, cdiv, c0)), wn(wcel(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), cq)))
  eldifbd(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), cq, cr, w0)
  syl2anc(w0, wcel(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), cdif(cr, cq)), wcel(nat2, cprime), wcel(c3, cfv(cuz, nat2)))
  a1i(w0, wcel(nat2, cprime))
  2prm()
  syl(w0, wcel(c3, cfv(cuz, nat2)), wcel(c3, cfv(cuz, nat3)))
  uzuzle23(c3)
  rtprmirr(nat2, c3)
  necon3bd(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), co(c2, cdiv, c0), w0, wcel(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), cq))
  syl(w0, wi(wceq(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), co(c2, cdiv, c0)), wcel(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), cq)), wcel(co(c2, cdiv, c0), cq))
  syl2anc(w0, wcel(co(c2, cdiv, c0), cq), wcel(c2, cz), wcel(c0, cn))
  nnzd(c2, w0)
  znq(c2, c0)
  eleq1a(co(c2, cdiv, c0), cq, co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)))
  exp11d(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), co(c2, cdiv, c0), c3, wa(w0, wceq(c0, c1)))
  adantr(w0, wceq(c0, c1), wcel(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), crp))
  rpcxpcld(nat2, co(nat1, cdiv, c3), w0)
  a1i(w0, wcel(nat2, crp))
  2rp()
  nnrecred(c3, w0)
  adantr(w0, wceq(c0, c1), wcel(co(c2, cdiv, c0), crp))
  rpdivcld(c2, c0, w0)
  nnrpd(c2, w0)
  nnrpd(c0, w0)
  3syl(wa(w0, wceq(c0, c1)), wcel(c3, cz), w0, wcel(c3, cfv(cuz, nat3)))
  simpl(w0, wceq(c0, c1))
  adantr(w0, wceq(c0, c1), wne(c3, nat0))
  nnne0d(c3, w0)
  3eqtr4d(co(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), cexp, c3), co(co(c2, cdiv, c0), cexp, c3), nat2, co(co(c2, cexp, c3), cdiv, co(c0, cexp, c3)), wa(w0, wceq(c0, c1)))
  mvllmuld(nat2, co(c2, cexp, c3), co(c0, cexp, c3), wa(w0, wceq(c0, c1)))
  adantr(w0, wceq(c0, c1), wne(co(c0, cexp, c3), nat0))
  expne0d(c0, c3, w0)
  syl(w0, wcel(c3, cz), wcel(c3, cfv(cuz, nat3)))
  eluzelz(c3, nat3)
  3eqtrd(co(co(c0, cexp, c3), cmul, nat2), co(c2, cexp, c3), co(co(c0, cexp, c3), caddc, co(c0, cexp, c3)), co(co(c0, cexp, c3), caddc, co(c1, cexp, c3)), wa(w0, wceq(c0, c1)))
  times2d(co(c0, cexp, c3), wa(w0, wceq(c0, c1)))
  adantr(w0, wceq(c0, c1), wcel(co(c0, cexp, c3), cc))
  expcld(c0, c3, w0)
  oveq2d(co(c0, cexp, c3), caddc, co(c0, cexp, c3), co(c1, cexp, c3), wa(w0, wceq(c0, c1)))
  oveq1d(c0, cexp, c3, c1, wa(w0, wceq(c0, c1)))
  simpr(w0, wceq(c0, c1))
  adantr(w0, wceq(c0, c1), wceq(co(co(c0, cexp, c3), caddc, co(c1, cexp, c3)), co(c2, cexp, c3)))
  syl2anc(wa(w0, wceq(c0, c1)), wceq(co(co(nat2, ccxp, co(nat1, cdiv, c3)), cexp, c3), nat2), wcel(nat2, cc), wcel(c3, cn))
  2cnd(wa(w0, wceq(c0, c1)))
  adantr(w0, wceq(c0, c1), wcel(c3, cn))
  cxproot(nat2, c3)
  adantr(w0, wceq(c0, c1), wceq(co(co(c2, cdiv, c0), cexp, c3), co(co(c2, cexp, c3), cdiv, co(c0, cexp, c3))))
  expdivd(c2, c0, c3, w0)
  nncnd(c2, w0)
  nncnd(c0, w0)
  nnne0d(c0, w0)
  nnnn0d(c3, w0)
  syl(w0, wcel(c3, cn), wcel(c3, cfv(cuz, nat3)))
  eluzge3nn(c3)
}
